################################################################################
# mdcolon Results Directory (.gitignore)
#
# This .gitignore applies ONLY to results/mcolon/
# Does NOT impact nlmaers or other users' results.
#
# Strategy: WHITELIST approach
# - Deny everything by default (prevents .npy, .pkl, checkpoints, etc.)
# - Explicitly allow source files and documentation
# - Safe and predictable
################################################################################

# Deny everything by default
/*
!*/
!**/

# ============================================================================
# SOURCE CODE & NOTEBOOKS (ALLOW)
# ============================================================================
!*.py           # Python scripts
!**/*.py        # Python scripts in subdirectories
!*.ipynb        # Jupyter notebooks
!*.md           # Markdown documentation
!*.txt          # Text files
!*.yml          # YAML config
!*.yaml
!*.json         # JSON config/data
!*.sh           # Shell scripts

# ============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION & CONFIG (ALLOW)
# ============================================================================
!.gitignore     # This file
!**/.gitignore  # Nested .gitignore files
!README*        # README files
!LICENSE
!MANIFEST.in

# ============================================================================
# KEY RESULTS (ALLOW - tracking important outputs)
# ============================================================================
# Allow ALL files in key_results/ directories at any depth
!**/key_results/
!**/key_results/**

# ============================================================================
# AUTOMATICALLY IGNORED (PREVENT ACCIDENTAL COMMITS)
# ============================================================================
# Binary/large files:
# - .npy (NumPy arrays)
# - .pkl, .pickle (pickled objects)
# - .pt, .pth (PyTorch models)
# - .h5 (HDF5)
# - *.ckpt (Checkpoints)
# - *.log (Logs)
# - *.pdb (Debugger)
# - *.png, *.jpg, *.jpeg, *.pdf, *.html, *.mp4
#
# These are implicitly ignored by the whitelist above.
